  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Tracking clean cookstoves &amp; fuel in Haiti</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Public-Private Alliance Foundation (PPAF) is building evidence on innovations for clean cooking in Haiti. Most families endure a poverty-respiratory disease-deforestation trap of dependence on charcoal for cooking. PPAF &amp; collaborators are conducting R&amp;D about solar cookstoves &amp; biodigesters for biogas &amp; garden fertilizer. This aims to promote sustainable development, empower women &amp; girls &amp; combat climate change.  COVID-19 attacks the respiratory system, giving all increased importance.</narrative>
  </description>
